                "          Michigan"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,RCA,101,339,2013",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,RCA,101,339,2013",
                    "doi": "10.1524/ract.2013.2031",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "RCA",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "101",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "339"
                      },
                      "date": 2013
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USALAS"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed at the Los",
                "Alamos Isotope Production Facility (LANL-IPF), which",
                "uses 100 MeV proton beam, extracted from the main 800",
                "MeV LANSCE proton linear accelerator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Target stack configuration consisting of WO3 target",
                "in degrader assembly with cooling water. The stack",
                "components are",
                "Material    Thickness Entry energy Exit energy  dE",
                "             (mm)       (MeV)         (MeV)    (MeV)",
                "Inconel        0.64     100.0          97.2      2.8",
                "Cooling water  5.0       97.2          93.4      3.9",
                "Al degrader   12.4       93.4          71.3     22.1",
                "Cooling water  5.0       71.3          66.4      4.9",
                "Al degrader   10.5       66.4          40.3     26.1",
                "Cooling water  5.0       40.3          32.1      8.2",
                "Nb             0.6       32.1          26.3      5.8",
                "WO3            2.5       26.3          9.7      16.6",
                "Nb             1.4        9.7          Stopped   9.7",
                "Water          5.0        n/a          n/a       n/a",
                "The natWO3 powder target, 25.19 g original mass,",
                "5.1 cm dia x 2.54 mm thick, encapsulated in Nb shell",
                "windows with thicknesses of 0.6 mm front and 1.4 mm",
                "back.",
                "The tungsten oxide puck was prepared by pressing (force",
                "200 kN or 20.4 t of weight) and sintering (heating in",
                "air at 1000deg C) of the powder and then sealing it",
                "inside the capsule under vacuum by means of electron",
                "beam welding."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Ortec Model GMX-35200-S HPGe detector. The",
                "detector diameter was 50.0 mm, detector length 53.5",
                "mm, resolution at 1333 keV was 1.99 keV, the relative",
                "efficiency at 1333 keV was about 10%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Stack target geometry configuration was used to to",
                "degrade the beam energy, the roughly Gaussian shaped",
                "proton energy distribution at the target is expected",
                "to be significantly broadened (up to +-6MeV FWHM).",
                "Mean proton energies within a target stack was",
                "determined from radioisotope formation ratios,",
                "assuming that the excitation function for those",
                "isotopes is well known. The beam current was chosen",
                "conservatively and had an average of 18.50+-0.02 mu-A."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " WO3 mass was weighed and dissolved in",
                "NaOH solution.The filtered Na2WO4 solution was then",
                "loaded onto an anion exchange column  (Bio-Rad",
                " AG 1 x 8, resin bed column of 1.2 cm",
                "diameter x 13.3 cm length, pre-equilibrated with NaOH,",
                "1 mol dm-3). The isotope 187W was used as a tracer",
                "for tungsten throughout the separation experiment.",
                "Rhenium isotopes were quantitatively retained, while",
                "the Na2WO4 matrix solution eluted. This final product",
                "was assayed for W, Ta, Hf and Re concentration via",
                "ICP-AES. An aliquot (2.29 g of solution out of 20.0 g",
                "total mass) was diluted with HCl (up to a",
                "total of 5.0 g, 0.1 mol dm-3) for analyses.",
                "Raw instrument results were corrected for dilution",
                "and total target mass. Final product activities",
                "measured by gamma ray spectroscopy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
